  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a study to determine what Human Papillomavirus HIV seropositive women in Botswana,
      South Africa and Brasil have been exposed to during their life. The Human Papillomavirus
      causes cervical cancer. Different types are more likely to lead to cancer than other types. A
      vaccine has been made to fight infection against HPV 16 and 18 which has been shown to cause
      cervical cancer in America and Europe. What HPV type cause cancer in other countries is not
      as well studied.

      Hypothesis HPV serology will demonstrate that exposure to each HPV type in Gardisil
      (6,11,16,18) will be &lt;50% in HIV seropositive women in resource limited countries.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Plasma from HIV seropositive women will be taken and sent to MERCK in the USA to evaluate
      what the antibody titers of HPV 6,11,16 and 18. .
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
